FIG. 1 is a block diagram showing an apparatus for reproducing audio data for a motion picture film according to the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a partial plan view of the motion picture film for illustrating a digital sound track and letters for identification recorded on the motion picture film;


FIG. 3 illustrates the manner in which film blocks formed by the interleaving technique may be recorded on the motion picture film of FIG. 1;


FIG. 4 illustrates the leading end data recorded on the motion picture film;


FIG. 5 is a diagram illustrating the size of an audio data dot recorded on the motion picture film;


FIG. 6 is a graph to which reference will be made in explaining the relationship between the dot size and error correction capability;


FIG. 7 is a graph for illustrating light emitting characteristics of a red-hued light emitting diode provided in the audio data reproducing apparatus and light receiving characteristics of a CCD line sensor;


FIGS. 8A to 8C are timing charts for illustrating the turn-on timing of the light emitting diode provided on the audio data reproducing apparatus and the readout timing of the CCD line sensor;


FIG. 9 illustrates film blocks symmetrically recorded on the right-channel sound track and the left-channel digital sound track of the motion picture film;


FIG. 10 is a block diagram of a tracking error system of the reproducing apparatus for controlling the readout timing of the CCD line sensor for correcting the tracking error associated with the left channel;


FIGS. 11A to 11B are diagrams to which reference will be made in explaining tracking error of CCD line sensor(s) in reproducing audio data from the motion picture film;


FIG. 12 is a diagram to which reference will be made in explaining the timing of sample-holding the tracking pattern and azimuth check pattern by the tracking error system of FIG. 27;


FIG. 13 is a graph illustrating a driving pulse of the CCD line sensor formed by the tracking error correction system;


FIG. 14 is a schematic longitudinal cross-sectional view showing the construction of a light source to be used in substitution for the light emitting diode in the audio data reproducing apparatus;


FIG. 15 is a schematic perspective view showing the construction of a light source for reading out optical data according to the present invention.
